i see the get will return a collection of shares for the given file.

okay - this is far away from rest - i'm find with such an api if we stop calling it restful.

if we go out with this as restful api :-1:

all tests which are failing now are not related to the share api... for some reasons some encryption tests fails here. if they also fail on master after the merge i will take care of it. for this pull request they are out of scope, it would be great to finish the review process in time for the feature freeze.

@deepdiver1975 are you fine with it so far?

who wants to be the second reviewer? @blizzz @butonic @bantu @kondou-ger @kabum @bartv2 @icewind1991  or someone from the desktop developers who will use the api in the future... @dragotin @danimo ? of course everyone else is also welcome to review it. thanks a lot!

@deepdiver1975 hm, not really. it seems like the share exists, otherwise we couldn't generate the parameters for the function call: https://github.com/owncloud/core/pull/4877/files#l4r252 

i assume that something gets wrong when we try to get the source of the item, otherwise the error wouldn't be triggered: https://github.com/owncloud/core/blob/333d3eda993a2af26639cb73d60a79fb9322826b/apps/files_sharing/lib/api.php#l220 but i don't see what could be wrong with this db statement: https://github.com/owncloud/core/blob/333d3eda993a2af26639cb73d60a79fb9322826b/apps/files_sharing/lib/api.php#l449

